# KMP Stack

Always use:

- Clean Architecture (see `architecture.mdc`)
- Feature-first organization under `shared/feature/{name}/`
- Repository pattern
- MVVM with ViewModel + immutable UI state
- StateFlow for UI state
- Coroutines for async work
- Koin for dependency injection
- Compose Multiplatform for UI
- Kotlin Serialization for models
- Ktor Client for networking

# Feature Layout

Every feature must contain:

```text
shared/feature/{name}/
  domain/        # use cases, repository interfaces, domain models
  data/          # repository implementations, API clients, mappers
  presentation/  # ViewModel, UiState, Composables/Screens
  di/            # Koin module
  tests/
```

# Rules

- Never place business logic inside Composables.
- UI state must be immutable data classes.
- ViewModels expose StateFlow; Composables collect and render.
- Use `expect/actual` only when platform-specific behavior is required.
- Prefer `commonMain` for shared logic.
- Use platform source sets (`androidMain`, `iosMain`) only for native integrations.
- Follow Kotlin coding conventions.
- Extend existing feature packages before creating new ones.

# Prohibited

- Business logic in Composables or UI event handlers beyond delegation to ViewModel.
- Direct API calls from presentation layer.
- Duplicate repository or use-case implementations across features.
